The pound rose sharply, according to data indicating an increase in UK wage growth, while the FTSE 100 was boosted by the SABMiller bid target.
Earnings without bonuses in the United Kingdom grew by 2.9% between May and July compared to the same period last year.
This percentage has been the fastest and most accurate estimate of the time of interest rate increase since 2009.
