SABMiller was the outstanding share in the market, making a 20% leap after the takeover bid from rival AB InBev.
A transaction would combine the two largest breweries in the world and bring together brands such as Budweiser, Stella Artois, Peroni and Grolsch.
Burberry shares were 0.9% higher, according to encouraging news from the Richemont luxury competitors.
